<hr size=10>
<h2>86級畢業碩士　張恩杰　發表論文</h2>
<hr size=5>

<CENTER>
<h3><A NAME=AIC>模糊類神經網路的效率驗證以及效能提昇之研究</A></h3>
<h4>摘要</h4>
</CENTER>
<blockquote>
       Knowledge-Based Neural Network with Trapezoidal Fuzzy Set 
      (KBNN/TFS) 是一個模糊類神經網路模型，它能處理梯形表示法的模
      糊輸入資料，以及具有對模糊規則做修正、正確性驗證與產生的能
      力。與產生的能力。根據KBNN/TFS我們提出一個用以評估規則推論
      之複雜度的效率驗證方法；此外，為了增進模糊規則的推論效率，
      效率，我們另提出了三種方法簡化這種由模糊規則構成的類神經網
      路。第一種方法稱為fuzzy tabulation method，此種方法是以修改
      規則的前提部分來達到規則間的合併，並且能去除規則中不須考慮
      的變數 (don*t care variables)。第二種方法稱為transitive
      fuzzy rule compacting method，它將具有遞移性的規則合併，以
      減少推論時的計算量。第三種方法稱為identical antecedent 
      unifying method，為了簡化規則中重複的前提，它將規則中相同
      的前提以一個特別的前提取代，並且插入一條新的規則來推論
      這個特別的前提。經由這些方式，規則的結構能夠被簡化，而
      且不會改變其推論的結果。我們用提出的效率驗證方法分析及
      證實這三種效率增進方法的結果。實驗結果顯示，經過這三種
      效率增進方法的處理，規則推論的效率增強了許多。
</blockquote>

<HR SIZE=3 WIDTH=80%>

<CENTER>
<h3><A NAME=AIE>Efficiency Validation of Fuzzy Domain Theories Using a Neural Network Model</A></h3>
<h4>Abstract</h4>
</CENTER>
<blockquote>
 Knowledge-Based Neural Network with Trapezoidal Fuzzy Set (KBNN/TFS) is 
a fuzzy neural network model, which handles trapezoidal fuzzy inputs with the 
abilities of fuzzy rule revision, verification and generation.  Based on 
KBNN/TFS, an efficiency validation method is proposed to evaluate the rule 
inference complexity on KBNN/TFS.  Besides, three methods that simplify the 
structure of this fuzzy rule-based neural network model are provided to enhance 
the inference efficiency.  Fuzzy tabulation method, the first method, is 
performed to do rule combination by modifying the antecedents of some specific 
rules and then to eliminate the don*t care variables in the rules.  The second 
method, named transitive fuzzy rule compacting method, combines the rules that 
have the transitive relations to decrease the computational load of inference.  
The third method, called identical antecedent unifying method, simplifies the 
redundant antecedents of rules by replacing the identical ones of the rules with a 
single specific antecedent.  Another rule with those replaced antecedents is 
inserted to imply the specific antecedent which is used to replace the redundant 
ones.  By this method, the structure of rules can be simplified without change 
the results of its inference.  The proposed efficiency validation method is used 
to analyze and support the results of performing these three efficiency enhancing
methods.  Also the simulation results show that the efficiency is 


</blockquote>

